Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Create Profile (UC2), Upload Photo (UC5), include relationship from UC2 to UC5
   Explanation: The use case "Upload Photo" (UC5) is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Create Profile" / UC2). It is not associated with any actor directly. It neither includes nor extends any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is neither a generalization nor a specialization of any use case. "Upload Photo" does not represent a complete, standalone service observable to any actor — it is merely a decomposed sub-step of the profile creation process. This constitutes the "Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship" antipattern, where the service of creating a profile has been improperly split into a separate inclusion use case that has no independent value.
